# Copy to `.env` in this folder for local / phone-on-LAN testing.
# Find your PC IP: Windows `ipconfig` → IPv4 (e.g. 192.168.1.42)
#
# When opening the app on your phone at http://YOUR_IP:3000, the API URL must
# point to your PC — not localhost (that would be the phone itself).
#
# VITE_API_URL=http://192.168.1.42:3001/api/v1
#
# PRODUCTION: VITE_API_URL is REQUIRED. Deploy builds (Vercel/CI) fail without
# it (see vite.config.js), and a production bundle refuses to boot without it
# (see src/utils/env.js). Example: VITE_API_URL=https://api.soloway.app/api/v1

# Optional: Sentry error monitoring (frontend project DSN from sentry.io).
# Leave unset to disable. Safe to expose — DSNs are public identifiers.
# VITE_SENTRY_DSN=https://examplePublicKey@o0.ingest.sentry.io/0
